# ============================================
# Life OS — Environment Configuration
# ============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
#
# !! WARNING: .env IS A PUBLIC WEB ASSET — IT IS NOT A SECRET STORE !!
#
# pubspec.yaml declares .env as a Flutter asset, so it is copied VERBATIM
# into the web bundle and served publicly. Anyone can download it at
# https://lifeos.deadthrone.dev/assets/.env — no login, no obscurity.
#
# .env being gitignored makes it LOOK like the safe place for secrets.
# It is the exact opposite: a committed secret is at least private to the
# repo, while a secret placed here is broadcast to the open internet.
#
# NO SECRET OF ANY KIND MAY GO IN THIS FILE. Specifically NEVER add:
#   - the Supabase service_role key (bypasses RLS = full database access)
#   - GROQ_API_KEY or any other AI/provider API key
#   - SMTP or database passwords
#   - admin tokens, session secrets, private keys
#
# Server-side secrets belong in Supabase Edge Function secrets
# (`npx supabase secrets set`), never here.
#
# ONLY browser-public values belong here — the three below and nothing
# more. Need a fourth key? STOP and ask before adding it.
# ============================================

# Supabase
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_publishable_key

# Google OAuth (Web Client ID)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
